## PROMPT 4 — HIGH: Fix PrismaClient Singleton Violation in Health Route

**Problem:**
`src/app/api/v1/health/route.ts` instantiates `new PrismaClient()` on every
single health check request:
```ts
const prisma = new PrismaClient();
try {
  await prisma.$queryRaw`SELECT 1`;
} finally {
  await prisma.$disconnect();
}
```
This creates a new database connection pool on each request, immediately
disconnects it, and forces PostgreSQL to accept a new connection on the next
call. Under any monitoring frequency (30s Caddy health interval + Uptime Robot
+ CI health checks), this causes dozens of unnecessary connection open/close
cycles per minute. The singleton from `src/lib/db.ts` already exists for exactly
this purpose.

**Task:** Refactor the health route to use the shared Prisma singleton and
enhance it with environment version reporting.

Requirements:
1. In `src/app/api/v1/health/route.ts`, replace `new PrismaClient()` with
   the singleton import:
   ```ts
   import { db } from '@/lib/db';
   ```
   Remove the local `const prisma = new PrismaClient()` and the
   `finally { await prisma.$disconnect() }` block entirely. The singleton
   manages its own connection pool — do not disconnect it.

2. Keep the `SELECT 1` health check but use the singleton:
   ```ts
   await db.$queryRaw`SELECT 1`;
   ```

3. Extend the health response to include `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION`:
   ```ts
   version: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION ?? process.env.npm_package_version ?? '0.2.0',
   ```
   This falls back to the npm package version from `process.env.npm_package_version`
   (automatically set by npm) so no additional env var configuration is needed.

4. Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION` to `src/lib/env.ts` in the `publicEnvSchema`:
   ```ts
   NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_VERSION: z.string().regex(/^\d+\.\d+\.\d+$/).optional(),
   ```

5. Add a simple response time measurement to the health check:
   ```ts
   const dbStart = Date.now();
   await db.$queryRaw`SELECT 1`;
   const dbLatencyMs = Date.now() - dbStart;
   ```
   Include `dbLatencyMs` in the checks object so monitoring can alert on
   slow database responses.

6. Also fix `src/app/api/health/db/route.ts` — it has the same `new PrismaClient()`
   anti-pattern. Apply the same singleton fix there.

7. Run `npm run typecheck` — must pass with zero errors.

Files to modify: `src/app/api/v1/health/route.ts`,
  `src/app/api/health/db/route.ts`, `src/lib/env.ts`

